    "summary": "I am an anthropologist, Latin Americanist and victimologist. My research explores whether and, if so, how legal, quasi-legal and non-legal transitional justice procedures affect the daily lives of those who experienced political violence, gross human rights violations and mass victimisation.\nI have a keen interest in the themes of:\t\n- Transitional justice, particularly the right to and politics of reparations\n- Participation, citizenship, state-survivors relations in post-conflict societies\n- Victim labelling and victim identities\n- Human rights, international justice\n- Alternative justice epistemologies and social comparison\n- Ethnography, phenomenological research, participatory research, visual methods, mixed-methods\n- Peru, Colombia, Cyprus, Guatemala, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Guinea-Conakry, Northern-Iraq\n- Latin America",
